Here is the Prisma schema and a structured outline of the API routes aligning with your AI Agent Management Platform plan.

```prisma
// prisma/schema.prisma

generator client {
  provider = "prisma-client-js"
}

datasource db {
  provider = "postgresql"
  url      = env("DATABASE_URL")
}

model Agent {
  id            String     @id @default(uuid())
  name          String     @unique
  status        AgentStatus @default(idle)
  lastHeartbeat DateTime
  metadata      Json?      // JSONB
  createdAt     DateTime   @default(now())
  updatedAt     DateTime   @updatedAt
  deployments   Deployment[]
  telemetry     AgentTelemetry[]
  swarms       SwarmAgent[]
}

model AgentSwarm {
  id          String        @id @default(uuid())
  name        String        @unique
  description String?
  createdAt   DateTime      @default(now())
  updatedAt   DateTime      @updatedAt
  agents      SwarmAgent[]
  tasks       Task[]
}

model SwarmAgent {
  swarm    AgentSwarm @relation(fields: [swarmId], references: [id])
  swarmId  String
  agent    Agent     @relation(fields: [agentId], references: [id])
  agentId  String

  @@id([swarmId, agentId])
}

model Task {
  id        String      @id @default(uuid())
  swarm     AgentSwarm  @relation(fields: [swarmId], references: [id])
  swarmId   String
  taskType  String
  payload   Json
  status    TaskStatus  @default(pending)
  result    Json? 
  createdAt DateTime    @default(now())
  updatedAt DateTime    @updatedAt
}

model Deployment {
  id          String      @id @default(uuid())
  agent       Agent       @relation(fields: [agentId], references: [id])
  agentId     String
  version     String
  status      DeploymentStatus @default(pending)
  deployedAt  DateTime?
  log         String?
  createdAt   DateTime    @default(now())
}

model AgentTelemetry {
  id          String   @id @default(uuid())
  agent       Agent    @relation(fields: [agentId], references: [id])
  agentId     String
  cpuUsage    Float?
  memoryUsage Float?
  networkIo   Json?
  timestamp   DateTime @default(now())
}

enum AgentStatus {
  idle
  running
  error
  offline
}

enum TaskStatus {
  pending
  running
  completed
  failed
}

enum DeploymentStatus {
  pending
  in_progress
  successful
  failed
}
```

---

# API Routes Outline

### Agents
- `GET /api/agents`  
  List all agents with their current status and metadata.

- `GET /api/agents/:id`  
  Get details of a single agent.

- `POST /api/agents`  
  Create/register a new agent.  
  Request body:  
  ```json
  {
    "name": "AgentName",
    "metadata": {...} // optional JSON
  }
  ```

- `PUT /api/agents/:id`  
  Update agent info or status.  
  Request body can include properties such as `status`, `metadata`, `lastHeartbeat`.

- `DELETE /api/agents/:id`  
  Remove an agent.

---

### Swarms
- `GET /api/swarms`  
  List all swarms.

- `POST /api/swarms`  
  Create a new swarm.  
  Request body:  
  ```json
  {
    "name": "SwarmName",
    "description": "Optional description"
  }
  ```

- `GET /api/swarms/:id`  
  Get swarm details including member agents.

- `PUT /api/swarms/:id`  
  Update swarm info.

- `DELETE /api/swarms/:id`  
  Delete a swarm.

- `POST /api/swarms/:id/agents`  
  Add agent(s) to swarm.  
  Request body:  
  ```json
  {
    "agent_ids": ["agent-uuid-1", "agent-uuid-2"]
  }
  ```

- `DELETE /api/swarms/:id/agents/:agentId`  
  Remove agent from swarm.

---

### Tasks
- `GET /api/tasks`  
  List all tasks with their statuses.

- `POST /api/tasks`  
  Create a new task assigned to a swarm.  
  Request body:  
  ```json
  {
    "swarm_id": "swarm-uuid",
    "task_type": "data_analysis",
    "payload": {...}
  }
  ```

- `GET /api/tasks/:id`  
  Retrieve task status and result.

- `PUT /api/tasks/:id`  
  Update task status/result (used by agents/reporters).

---

### Deployments
- `GET /api/deployments`  
  List all deployment records.

- `POST /api/deployments`  
  Trigger a deployment on an agent.  
  Request body:  
  ```json
  {
    "agent_id": "agent-uuid",
    "version": "1.0.0"
  }
  ```

- `GET /api/deployments/:id`  
  Get deployment logs and status.

---

### Telemetry (Monitoring)
- `GET /api/telemetry/agents/:agentId`  
  Retrieve recent telemetry data (historical) for an agent.

- WebSocket or SSE endpoint: `/ws/telemetry`  
  Streams real-time telemetry and live status updates of agents.

